 <section class="view" id="view-frameworks">
<h2 class="sec">What is an Organization?</h2>
<div class="note"><ul>
<li>A collective gathering of individuals and groups or teams.</li>
<li>Pursues clear goals and objectives shared by members.</li>
<li>Establishes strategies toward those goals — its <b>management models</b>.</li>
<li>Contains structure, processes and procedures that establish interactions and <b>distribute power</b>.</li>
<li>Has tacit and explicit norms, rules and practices that shape members' behavior.</li>
<li>Focuses on results through optimization — and <b>achieves its purpose through culture</b>.</li>
</ul></div>

<h2 class="sec">What is Culture?</h2>
<div class="note"><ul>
<li>The block of consistent and observable patterns of beliefs and behaviors within organizations.</li>
<li>A process of <b>"sense-making"</b> and a carrier of meaning.</li>
<li>A <b>social control system</b> — "what happens when managers leave the room."</li>
<li>A form of protection that evolved from situational pressures.</li>
<li>Powerfully shaped by incentives and by the broader societal context.</li>
</ul></div>

<h2 class="sec">Schein's Three Levels of Culture</h2>
<div class="fw">
 <div class="b"><b>1. Artifacts</b>The visible environment of a firm: architecture, technology, office layout, dress, behaviors. Easy to observe but hard to interpret.</div>
 <div class="b"><b>2. Espoused Values</b>The reasons / rationalizations for why members behave as they do. Often requires interviewing key members or consulting documents.</div>
 <div class="b"><b>3. Basic Underlying Assumptions</b>Taken-for-granted beliefs about truth, human nature, time and space — the ultimate source of values and action.</div>
</div>

<h2 class="sec">The Cultural "Iceberg"</h2>
<div class="iceberg">
 <div class="vis">Above the waterline — visible culture</div>
 <div class="row">Vision · Strategy · Shared values · Goals · Structures · Policies · Procedures — "the way we say we get things done"</div>
 <div class="inv">Below the waterline — invisible culture</div>
 <div class="row">Beliefs · Shared assumptions · Perceptions · Values · Norms · Unwritten rules · Stories · Feelings — "the way we really get things done"</div>
</div>

<h2 class="sec">Organizational Culture Components</h2>
<div class="note">A central <b>Leader</b>, surrounded by <b>Structure</b>, <b>People</b> and <b>Values</b> — all operating within <b>Context</b>.</div>

<h2 class="sec">Organizational Culture Types (Competing Values)</h2>
<div class="note"><div class="tag">Axes: Internal focus &amp; integration ↔ External focus &amp; differentiation; Flexibility &amp; discretion ↔ Stability &amp; control</div>
<div class="quad">
